// ERROR: E2440
// P0 borrowck-nll-foundation, Trụ 2 (alias propagation across Assign),
// 2026-07-18. A sub-borrow of `e`'s payload escapes its match arm via a
// plain reference `Assign` into the merge var `s` (contrast fixture 409,
// which only covers the reassign-WITHIN-the-SAME-arm case and explicitly
// notes this broader case was found UNGUARDED before this fix — no E2440,
// a real would-be UAF). Without Trụ 2, the loan created for `s`'s
// underlying reference stays anchored on the match-arm-local temporary,
// which dies at the arm's own end — so by the time `e` is reassigned
// after the match, the loan has already (wrongly) evaporated and the
// conflict is silently missed (alias-loss under-refuse). With Trụ 2, the
// loan is re-anchored onto `s` itself, so it is still active when `e` is
// reassigned while `s` is later read via `length(s)` — a genuine
// exclusivity violation (reassigning `e` would free the old payload `s`
// points into).
enum Msg { Ping(String), Pong }
function main() -> Integer {
    let mutable e = Msg::Ping("hi")
    let fallback = "none"
    let s = match &0 e {
        Msg::Ping(x) => x,
        Msg::Pong => &0 fallback,
    }
    e = Msg::Ping("bye")
    return length(s)
}
